Alright, here we go.
1. Electric eel is a very safe ride from personal perspective, and even though one person out of the other thousand reviews on this ride is a one star from ONE small incident, it is a great ride and shouldn’t be reviewed from other, you should personally
2. Manta was voted one of the best rides in the US one year, and one review from a guy that pointed out all the good things about a ride saying that they were bad isn’t a good enough excuse to call a ride that was voted such a reward bad. From personal experience on this ride, it’s a great one for everyone who isn’t a boomer with their kids
3. Journey to Atlantis is probably the worst out of the three, but still a good ride. Honestly could be better and even though it was the “best” out of what they heard, it’s not. Good ride, doesn’t deserve to be better. Don’t read things on reviews and expect a good or bad concept and lie while complaining after to make it look bad.
